---
---

<section class="py-20 sm:py-28 bg-navy-light">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">The Problem</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white">What's slowing your team down every month</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mt-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Document collection is still one of the most manual parts of running a CPA firm. Staff follow up with clients, check who replied, track what's still missing, and repeat the same reminders again and again.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-error/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-error" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Manual client chasing</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Your staff spends hours sending reminders, checking responses, and nudging clients again. It's repetitive, time-consuming, and keeps skilled accountants away from billable work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-warning/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-warning" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-2">No clear status visibility</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Important documents are scattered across WhatsApp chats, email, spreadsheets, and memory. Nobody has a clear picture of who sent what and what's still missing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-blue/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Last-minute deadline pressure</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Missing documents lead to delays, last-minute scrambles, and avoidable stress. Tax season becomes 60-hour weeks of chasing, not accounting.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
